TITLE: Implementing NativeWind with styled components in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use NativeWind's styled function to create styled components in React Native. It shows the basic setup for a simple app with styled View and Text components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/versioned_docs/version-v2/home.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styled } from 'nativewind';

const StyledView = styled(View)
const StyledText = styled(Text)

const App = () => {
  return (
    <StyledView className="flex-1 items-center justify-center">
      <StyledText className="text-slate-800">
        Try editing me! üéâ
      </StyledText>
    </StyledView>
  );
}
```

