TITLE: Creating Dynamic Styles with NativeWind in React Native
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create dynamic styles using conditional logic to build class names. This pattern allows for component styling to be controlled through props, making components more reusable and flexible.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/docs/home.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { Text } from "react-native";

export function MyText({ bold, italic, lineThrough, ...props }) {
  const classNames = [];

  if (bold) classNames.push("font-bold");
  if (italic) classNames.push("italic");
  if (lineThrough) classNames.push("line-through");

  return <Text className={classNames.join(" ")} {...props} />;
}
```

