TITLE: Comparing Third-Party Components with and without className Support in JSX
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the difference between components that don't pass the className prop (picking props) and those that correctly spread remaining props, allowing NativeWind to work properly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/docs/guides/third-party-components.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// ‚ùå This component will not work with NativeWind
// This component is 'picking' the props.
// Any props that are not explicitly defined will not be passed down
function ThirdPartyComponent({ style }) {
  return <View style={style} />;
}

// ‚úÖ This component will work with NativeWind
function ThirdPartyComponent({ style, ...props }) {
  return <View style={style} {...props} />;
}
```

