TITLE: Applying Platform-Specific Styles with NativeWind in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use platform-specific class names in NativeWind to apply different text colors based on the platform (iOS, Android, or web). It uses styled components from NativeWind and platform variants in the className prop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/versioned_docs/version-v2/core-concepts/platforms.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styled } from 'nativewind';

const StyledView = styled(View)
const StyledText = styled(Text)

const App = () => {
  return (
    <StyledView className="flex-1 items-center justify-center">
      <StyledText className={`
        ios:text-red-500
        android:text-blue-500
        web:text-green-600
      `}>
        Text color changes per Platform! üéâ
      </StyledText>
    </StyledView>
  );
}
```

