TITLE: Configuring Platform-Specific Colors in NativeWind
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to extend the Tailwind CSS theme configuration to include platform-specific colors using NativeWind's platformSelect and platformColor utilities. It shows how to define a custom 'error' color that adapts to iOS, Android, and provides a default fallback value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/docs/customization/colors.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// tailwind.config.js

const { platformSelect, platformColor } = require("nativewind/theme");

module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        error: platformSelect({
          // Now you can provide platform specific values
          ios: platformColor("systemRed"),
          android: platformColor("?android:colorError"),
          default: "red",
        }),
      },
    },
  },
};
```

