TITLE: Implementing Viewport Units with NativeWind in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use viewport units (vh) with NativeWind in a React Native application. It creates a styled View component with a height of 25vh and width of 50vh, containing centered text. The example showcases the integration of NativeWind's styled function with React Native components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/versioned_docs/version-v2/core-concepts/units.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styled } from 'nativewind';

const StyledView = styled(View)
const StyledText = styled(Text)

const App = () => {
  return (
    <StyledView className={`
      items-center
      justify-center
      bg-slate-300
      m-auto
      h-[25vh]
      w-[50vh]
    `}>
      <StyledText
        selectable={false}
        className="text-slate-800"
      >
        Rotate me! üéâ
      </StyledText>
    </StyledView>
  );
}
```

