TITLE: Implementing Flex Basis with NativeWind in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use flex basis classes in NativeWind to control the initial size of flex items. It creates a row of three boxes with different flex basis values, showcasing the distribution of space.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/versioned_docs/version-v2/tailwind/flexbox/flex-basis.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styled } from 'nativewind';

const StyledView = styled(View)
const StyledText = styled(Text)

const Box = ({ className, ...props }) => (
  <StyledText className={`flex text-center h-14 justify-center items-center text-white bg-fuchsia-500 rounded ${className}`} {...props}/>
)

const App = () => {
  return (
    <StyledView className="flex flex-row h-screen items-center space-x-2">
      <Box className="basis-1/4">01</Box>
      <Box className="basis-1/4">02</Box>
      <Box className="basis-1/2">03</Box>
    </StyledView>
  );
}
```

