TITLE: Implementing Flex Row Reverse Layout with NativeWind in React Native
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a reversed horizontal layout using flex-row-reverse in NativeWind. It creates a StyledView with flex-row-reverse class and renders three Box components inside it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nativewind/nativewind/blob/main/apps/website/versioned_docs/version-v2/tailwind/flexbox/flex-direction.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Text, View } from 'react-native';
import { styled } from 'nativewind';

const StyledView = styled(View)
const StyledText = styled(Text)

const Box = ({ className = '', ...props }) => (
  <StyledText className={`flex text-center h-14 w-14 m-2 justify-center items-center text-white bg-fuchsia-500 rounded ${className}`} {...props}/>
)

const App = () => {
  return (
    <StyledView className="flex flex-row-reverse h-screen">
      <Box>01</Box>
      <Box>02</Box>
      <Box>03</Box>
    </StyledView>
  );
}
```

